This paper deals with a dynamic facility location problem, which involves updating the solution as clients are inserted or deleted. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a deterministic algorithm that maintains a constant factor approximation to the optimal solution, which could fall under the Game Theory (cs.GT) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of metric spaces and doubling dimension also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) categories.
